gsml:GeologicUnit.gml:description: Black shale, minor sandstone: shale thick-bedded, rarely with soft-sediment folding; sandstone pale grey; thin to thick-bedded; fine to medium-grained; Tbc, Tc, minor Tabc turbidites; micaceous; shale commonly with rich lates Middle to Late Ordovician late Darriwilian to mid-Bolindian) graptolite faunas
gsml:GeologicUnit.gml:name: Mount Easton Shale (Oxe)

gsml:GeologicUnit.gml:description: Undifferentiated: sandstone, siltstone, black shale; sparsely fossiliferous

urn:cgi:feature:GSV:GeologicUnit:16777549126932776

gsml:GeologicUnit.gml:description: Sandstone, mudstone, black shale and minor granule quartz conglomerate: mostly thick- bedded sandstone, coarse- to fine-grained, often graded, diffusely stratified to cross laminated, moderately to well sorted; sparsely fossiliferous with graptolites and phyllocarids; deep marine turbidites and hemipelagic sediments

gsml:GeologicUnit.gml:description: Chert conglomerate, quartz sandstone: massive to diffusely stratified; conglomerate framework closed to open. massive to weakly bedded.
